Jackson Byrnes was told he had a stage four brain tumour three weeks ago . 
  The Casino teenager underwent a risky operation to remove the tumour on Wednesday . 
  Renowned neurosurgeon Dr Charlie Teo was the only surgeon in Australia willing to perform the risky operation . 
  The surgery will likely leave the 18-year-old paralysed . 
  His family raised $95,000 for the $80,000 operation . 
  Jackson woke up from the surgery able to move his body and thank his surgeon . 
  His mother Rhonda said the surgery was a success . 
 